steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"a0ld","text":"- Perform a 3 ml YPD (yeast extract 10g/l, bacto peptone 10g/l, glucose 10g/l) culture for 60h in order to harvest cells at stationary phase.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"b19ig","text":"- Centrifuge 5 min at 5000 rpm and remove the supernatant.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"efcv","text":"- Wash the pellet with 5 ml of 50mM EDTA, transfer to a 2 ml screw cap tube and centrifuge for 5 min at 12000 rpm. Remove the supernatant.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5kt0l","text":"- Add 0.2ml lysis buffer (50mM Tris pH 8, 50mM EDTA, 100mM NaCl, 2% Triton, 1% SDS), 0.2ml TE 1X (10mM Tris pH 8, 1mM EDTA), 0.2ml phenol/chloroform and 0.3g glass beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5v5q4","text":"- Grind with the Digital Disruptor Genie (Scientific Industries, Bohemia, NY 11716 U.S.A) for 2 minutes at 2850 rpm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dd1np","text":"- Centrifuge 5 min at 12000 rpm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2mlhq","text":"- Transfer the aqueous phase to a new tube, add 0.5 ml of chloroform and mix.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"b8r8l","text":"- Centrifuge 5 min at 12000 rpm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"esg25","text":"- Transfer the aqueous phase to a new tube, add 0.5 ml of isopropanol and mix.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4msbe","text":"- Centrifuge for 5 min at 12000 rpm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"82dea","text":"- Wash the pellet with 0.4 ml of 70% ethanol and let the tube dry.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c6qba","text":"- Re-suspend the DNA pellet in 490 µL of TE 1X and let overnight at 4 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5jrnu","text":"- Add 10 μl of RNase (100 mg/ml, Qiagen ref: 19101). Incubate for 60 min at 37 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f0d8l","text":"- To each sample, add 50 μl of 5 M NaCl, 15 μl of Chemagic CMG-252-A magnetic bead (PerkinElmer, Waltham, Massachusetts, U.S.A) suspension, 250 μl of 7.8M Guanidium chloride and 800 μl of isopropanol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"48j52","text":"- Mix by inversion for 5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dackr","text":"- Set up the tubes on the magnetic rack (DynaMag™-2 Magnet type, Invitrogen ThermoFisher Scientific).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"b36cm","text":"- Wait for 2 min. Remove the liquid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cb1h9","text":"- Perform a first wash with 1 ml of AMMLAV/E buffer (10 mM Tris pH 8.0, 0.1 mM EDTA, 60 mM potassium acetate, 65% ethanol) and mix gently to disintegrate the beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1bkls","text":"- Place the tubes on the magnetic rack. Wait 2 min. Remove the liquid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5i71q","text":"- Repeat a second wash with 1 ml of AMMLAV/E buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"80e9d","text":"- Perform two more washes as above with 1 ml of 75% ethanol","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6enn9","text":"- Air dry the beads at room temperature for 5 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"92lg4","text":"- Add 0.1 ml of 1X TE. Mix well to re-suspend the beads in TE 1X. Incubate 10 min at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a2otd","text":"- Place the tubes on the magnetic rack. Wait 5 min. Transfer the DNA solution to new storage tubes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1jpk","text":"- The DNAs are then stored at -20°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
